Video Recording:
LOOM: Very simple, free if signing up with University email
OBS: Slightly difficult but much more options and youtube tutorials
Bandicam: Free version has watermark & 10 minute limit, Easy but be careful when recording with voice
Xbox game bar: comes with windows, unstable
Microsoft powerpoint

Video Editor:
AVIDemux: Limited function but quick
Videopad 
Video Editor: Comes with Photos app on Windows 
Lightworks: Easy, lightweight but needs weekly registering

Audio:
Audacity (Chris's compressor settings):
Peace + Equalizer APO for external mics on win10


ActivePresenter - Lots of options but slightly slow on AIUB laptop

Flowchart/Circuit drawer:
draw.io: Available both online and as download

Physical Circuit simulation on breadboard
TinkerCAD: Online only, also features 3D design
Fritzing: Offline, less advanced than TinkerCAD

Regular simulation:
Falstad Java http://falstad.com/circuit/circuitjs1.zip 
(Physics ones https://www.falstad.com/mathphysics.html)
Online http://lushprojects.com/circuitjs/circuitjs.html

Not friendly https://easyeda.com/


To draw on screen:
ppInk
gInk
Pointofix
Epic Pen
ZoomIt

